# Upstream bug: https://github.com/libcheck/check/issues/360
# Upstream fix (open PR, not yet released): https://github.com/libcheck/check/pull/361
#
# A @verbatim block for the cmake -Dcheck_ROOT example was opened but never
# closed with @end verbatim. With Texinfo 7.x this became a hard error:
#   check.texi:2256: no matching `@end verbatim'
# which cascades into further node/menu errors and aborts the build.
#
# The bug was introduced in commit 56c347d ("Instructions how to import into
# CMake 3 project", 2019-05-11) and is present in all releases through 0.15.2.
# Upstream PR #361 (cherry-picked here) adds the missing @end verbatim.
diff --git a/doc/check.texi b/doc/check.texi
--- a/doc/check.texi
+++ b/doc/check.texi
@@ -2255,6 +2255,7 @@ your CMake build how to find it:

 @verbatim
 cmake -Dcheck_ROOT=${INSTALL_PREFIX}
+@end verbatim

 Then use Check in your @file{CMakeLists.txt} like this:

 @verbatim
